Ugandans Riot After Opposition Leader's Arrest
KAMPALA, Ugandaâ€”Hundreds of protesters rioted in the Ugandan capital, Kampala, on Thursday after the arrest of the country's main opposition leader, Kizza Besigye, during protests against rising food and fuel prices.
